is something I can use?

49:19.833 --> 49:24.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID SEDARIS: I flew here
from London. I was at Newark
Airport waiting for someone

49:24.033 --> 49:26.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to pick me up.

49:26.066 --> 49:29.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I saw a couple, and they
were in their mid-60s. And
then she said to him, where's

49:29.800 --> 49:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the other suitcase? And he
said, what other suitcase? She
said, you left home dragging

49:36.800 --> 49:40.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
two suitcases behind you. Now
you have got one. The other one
is mine. Where's my suitcase?

49:41.500 --> 49:43.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You lost my suitcase.

49:43.533 --> 49:47.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I thought, wow. I mean, I have
been in a similar situation,
right? And just the entire look

49:50.766 --> 49:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on her face, like, if I could
leave you now, or if I could
kill you now, I would do it.

49:57.766 --> 50:01.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I had to write about
that. Maybe one day, I would
write a story about arguing in

50:07.266 --> 50:12.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
public, and those would
come in handy in some way.

50:14.300 --> 50:17.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's also, like, if I were
going to remember yesterday,
I flew here in an airplane and

50:21.300 --> 50:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I did this and that. But that
was really the moment yesterday
where I felt like I was living

50:29.333 --> 50:34.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my life, like I was in the
moment. I wasn't thinking about
the past or about the future.

50:36.333 --> 50:39.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was just right there living,
visiting and listening, watching
those people have an argument.

50:43.233 --> 50:46.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And that sense
is important to you somehow?

50:46.566 --> 50:51.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID SEDARIS: Well, because I
spend so much time like living
in the past or the future.

50:53.600 --> 50:57.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, I think most people
do, really. And the moments
when you're really present in

50:59.333 --> 51:02.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
your life can be
pretty rare, really.

51:02.366 --> 51:07.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Sedaris'
